##Dictating | for the 15th time, I finally knocked on the door and my shoes were worn out

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Say Not tired affirmation is false, but again tired, also have to insist. If we do our job properly, the health of our residents will be better protected. I hope this outbreak is over.

Dictation | Zhou Rong

Finishing | Ying Chen

I am the General Secretary of the Party branch of Sanxing residential area, Zhijiang West Road Street, Jing 'an district. To be honest, the pressure of prevention and control at the grass-roots level is quite great. I've been working here for 11 years, and this is the first time I've faced an epidemic of this magnitude. Without experience, many jobs are also doing while fumbling. I have not rested since the New Year's Eve, and the rest of our neighborhood committee has not stopped since the third day of junior high school.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
SHŪEI's putting up health notices

On January 25th, the first day of my shift, I received a report that there might be a problem at a hotel in my district. I immediately went to the hotel to verify that there was an old couple from Yunmeng County, Hubei. Their son is rented to live in our community, because the home space is small, the old couple live in the hotel, has been a few days. I immediately reported the situation to the street.

In fact, the publicity work carried out by our neighborhood committee is still relatively early. Years ago, relevant notices were posted, asking residents to register with the neighborhood committee if they returned from Hubei Province. On the morning of the second day of the Lunar New Year, a resident called to say that his family had just returned from visiting relatives in Xiangyang, Hubei Province, on the first night of the Lunar New Year, because they saw our posters and knew that the situation needed to be notified to the Neighborhood Committee.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Health promotion in the district

Two things in a row, let me feel very flustered, do not know at heart, do not know how many residential areas in the end such a situation. Because at that time, we got the suspicious list from the top down, but not from the bottom up of the community. If someone is not so self-conscious reported, he came back from Hubei or close contact with the history of hiding at home, if he also out and about... the consequences of this is very serious, may be the block.

With this in mind, I immediately let all the third day to work, we held a meeting, ready to our residential areas under the jurisdiction of the three residents of 1536 households to conduct a comprehensive investigation.

On January 28th, starting at 8 am, eight of us, in groups of two, went to the houses of the residents in designated blocks to knock on their doors. We decided we didn't have enough time, and to increase our efficiency, we went back to working alone, supporting others until 8 p.m. , as soon as someone had finished subcontracting their own block. The next day we visited all the remaining families of the previous day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The neighborhood committee went door to door to register

In the first sweep, we probably knocked on over 800 doors. One is to register where they have been, there is no relevant contact history in Wuhan, the other is to suggest that they reduce travel, do a good job of personal protection, if necessary can contact the neighborhood committee. For those who do not knock, we will put a note on the door, please see them the first time contact the neighborhood committee.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For residents who didn't open their doors, Shūei put up a "note. " 

We asked for a 100 per cent "face-to-face" , either knocking on the door to see ourselves or getting a call from them when they saw the message. For those who did not "meet" , we later knocked on the door twice a day, in the morning and in the afternoon, until it opened.

In one of the houses I was in charge of, a note was torn up on the door, but the door would not be opened. After I knocked about seven or eight times, the security guard downstairs and the neighbors all told me that their house was occupied. I was so worried, I didn't know what was going on in their house. At that time, I was full of breath, two times a day is not enough, then come three times, I do not believe knock on your door.

Finally, on the 15th occasion, the House opened. I let out a sigh of relief and blurted out, "go get'EM, Amado! "

To learn more, we learned that in the early days, the couple were at home, but we didn't open the door because we weren't sure who we were, and we were afraid of getting infected. Later, sometimes they would go to the children's house to help with their grandchildren, but they weren't home. But see our community and closed the door, and prohibited take-out and express delivery in, think actually quite safe, this just rest assured to open the door for us.

Although it added to the trouble of our work, when I left, I praised their caution. You can't be too careful when you're dealing with an epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Residents Committee staff to check into the registration of the district

In addition to the couple, my colleagues also found a family in the sweep of people from Hubei. The man who answered the door said he had never been out of Shanghai, but my colleague saw two other people in the room. After repeated questioning, the other side admitted that he was from Hubei. As soon as I saw the name on the registration, I realized that they were the same old couple I had tracked down at the hotel the other day. After the hotel turned them off, they went to live with their son. My colleague said that the couple said, "you guys are so fast. I just moved in yesterday afternoon, and you caught me. ".

After the sweep, we'll have a meeting every day to update you. One time, I was in a meeting, and I looked down, and all my shoes were ripped. They also looked at the shoes they were wearing and noticed varying degrees of wear and tear. Because to walk, people are basically staring at the same pair of shoes fit.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Frayed shoes

For the two hubei-related residents found, medical care by the community hospital, CDC teachers in charge. And Our neighborhood committee, every day in addition to at least make a phone call, buy food, take express delivery and other needs of life are sure to pack.

So far (February 5) , there are about 246 households. We haven't been able to reach them. Now that number is dropping every day. The next is back to Shanghai Peak, we will follow up. Similarly, there is the jurisdiction of the resumption of work, we will actively cooperate with the property, to carry out related work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Residents who come to order face masks are required to have their temperature taken before entering the house
